value.value: The amount of matter in the respiratory muscles that arise from the lower border of one rib and insert into the upper border of the adjoining rib.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the healthfulness of an organism.
The total proportion, quantity, or volume of fat in milk.
The proportion, quantity, or volume in milk of macromolecules consisting of long sequences of amino acids in peptide linkage.
The proportion or number of offspring born alive.
The proportion or number of offspring born in single or multiple births.
The degree to which the female displays the state of sexual excitement during which she is most receptive to mating.
The proportion or number of offspring that have died before birth process is completed.
The distance from point to point along the longest axis of the nipple.
The proportion or number of mammary gland projections containing the outlets of the milk ducts through which milk is excreted.
The distance around the external sac of skin that encloses the testes.
The proportion, quantity, or volume of the fat-storing tissue lining the cavity bounded by the abdominal walls, the diaphragm, and the pelvis, and surrounding the internal organs.
The amount of matter in either or both of the muscles that make up the upper and fore part of the chest that adduct and rotate the arm and lift the ribs.
The amount of matter in the secondary, muscular stomach in some vertebrates used for grinding up food.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the morphology or physiology during formation and differentiation of the surface covering of birds, made of keratin.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to actions or reactions in tests for fear or anxiety related behaviors.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the pecking of the other birds.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the receipt of pecking by the other birds.
The two-dimensional extent of the bone of the forelimb that articulates with the scapula above and the radius and ulna below.

definition.value: calculated based on the length and width determined by x-ray densitometric scanning

value.value: The amount of matter in the minerals (inorganic elements or compounds that have importance in body functions) in the bone of the forelimb that articulates with the scapula above and the radius and ulna below.
The distance from side to side of the bone of the forelimb that articulates with the scapula above and the radius and ulna below.
The two-dimensional extent of the medial and larger of the two bones of the lower leg, which articulates with the femur, fibula, and talus.

definition.value: calculated based on the length and width determined by x-ray densitometric scanning

value.value: The amount of matter in the minerals (inorganic elements or compounds that have importance in body functions) in the medial and larger of the two bones of the lower leg, which articulates with the femur, fibula, and talus.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the ability of the medial and larger of the two bones of the lower leg to withstand the application of force without yielding or breaking.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the ability of the medial and larger of the two bones of the lower leg to recover size and shape after deformation in any way.
The distance from side to side of the medial and larger of the two bones of the lower leg, which articulates with the femur, fibula, and talus.
The proportion or number of eggs produced.
The distance around the metacarpal or metatarsal bone(s) in some hoofed mammals, extending between the knee or hock and the fetlock.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the physical magnitude of the long bone of the thigh.
The total number of bony segments constituting the vertebral column.
The proportion, quantity, or volume of the testicular steroid androstenone detected in the tissue composed of contractile cells or fibers that effects movement.
The amount of matter in the thin musculomebranous barrier that separates the abdominal and thoracic cavities.
The total amount of matter in all of the pedal extremities of an organism.
The amount of matter in the portion of the body containing the brain and organs of sight, hearing, taste, and smell.
The distance from point to point along the longest axis of the upper portion of the digestive tract, between the stomach and the large intestine.
The amount of matter in the membranous protective covering of the body.
The proportion, quantity, or volume of the compound produced from pyruvate by lactate dehydrogenase in the tissue composed of contractile cells or fibers that effects movement.
The proportion, quantity, or volume of the most abundant steroid in animal tissues present in the total lipid extracted from the contractile tissue that effects movement.
The proportion, quantity, or volume of indole, a tryptophan degradation product, detected in the tissue composed of contractile cells or fibers that effects movement.
The proportion, quantity, or volume of this clear, odorless, tasteless liquid in the tissue composed of contractile cells or fibers that effects movement.
The proportion, quantity, or volume of macromolecules consisting of long chains of amino acids in peptide linkage in the tissue composed of contractile cells or fibers that effects movement.
The proportion, quantity, or volume of skatole, a tryptophan degradation product, detected in the tissue composed of contractile cells or fibers that effects movement.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the ability of the contractile tissue that effects movement of an organ or part of the body to conduct electrical current.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the ability of the striated muscles connected at either or both extremities with the bony framework of the body to conduct electrical current.
The proportion, quantity, or volume of the testicular steroid androstenone present in fat tissue.
The proportion, quantity, or volume of fat-storing tissue present between the muscles.
The amount of matter in the fat-storing tissue associated with the digestive tube passing from the stomach to the anus.
The amount of matter in the fat-storing layer directly beneath the skin.

The proportion, quantity, or volume of fat-soluble substances (molecules composed of carbon and hydrogen and are characteristically insoluble in water) in the tissue composed of contractile cells or fibers that effects movement.
The amount of matter in the fat-storing cells/tissue present within skeletal muscle.
